title: Grateful Dead Live at Santa Fe Downs on 1983-09-11
lineage: MAC > Nak CR7A w/ azimuth adjusted > Korg MR-1000 @ 5.8mhz > FLAC 24/96; Edited & Mastered in Audacity by Joe Noel, Flac 24/96; Checksum & tags created in xACT
description:
Set 1

Alabama Getaway-> Greatest Story Ever Told, Dire Wolf, Hell In A Bucket, West L.A. Fadeaway, Me & My Uncle-> Mexicali Blues, Althea, CC Rider-> Might As Well

Set 2

Help On The Way-> Slipknot!-> Franklin's Tower-> Let It Grow-> He's Gone-> Drums-> Truckin'-> Wang Dang Doodle-> Morning Dew-> Around & Around-> Sugar Magnolia, E: U.S. Blues

reviews.review_text: Gem of an Aud. I had this source on tape for decades.  Undoubtedly got it from the Philly Crew in '84.  Know every note by heart.  The sound is haunting and fantastic.  Great crowd.  Absolutely one of the best shows of all time.  9/10 is more of the same.  I recently gave my entire tape collection to a friend, so thanks for uploading this source!  Great to hear this version again.  I think I prefer it to the SBD I have on disc.
